.TH "ath5k_ani_raise_immunity" 9 "ath5k_ani_raise_immunity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ath5k_ani_raise_immunity \- Increase noise immunity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ath5k_ani_raise_immunity
.BI "(struct ath5k_hw *ah "  ","
.BI "struct ath5k_ani_state *as "  ","
.BI "bool ofdm_trigger "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ah" 12
The \fIstruct ath5k_hw\fP
.IP "as" 12
The \fIstruct ath5k_ani_state\fP
.IP "ofdm_trigger" 12
If this is true we are called because of too many OFDM errors,
the algorithm will tune more parameters then.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Try to raise noise immunity (=decrease sensitivity) in several steps
depending on the average RSSI of the beacons we received.
